Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c\n+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c\n@@ -987,10 +987,16 @@\n \tif (intern->ptr != NULL && ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node != NULL) {\n-\t\tif (((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node)->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && ((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node)->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {\n-\t\t\tphp_libxml_node_decrement_resource((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);\n-\t\t} else {\n-\t\t\tphp_libxml_decrement_node_ptr((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);\n-\t\t\tretcount = php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref((php_libxml_node_object *)intern);\n-\t\t}\n-\t\tintern->ptr = NULL;\n+\t\txmlNodePtr n = ((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node);\n+\t\tif (n->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && n->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {\n+\t\t\tphp_libxml_node_decrement_resource((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);\n+\t\t} else {\n+\t\t\tphp_libxml_decrement_node_ptr((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);\n+\t\t\tretcount = php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref((php_libxml_node_object *)intern);\n+\t\t}\n+\t\tintern->ptr = NULL;\n+\t\t((php_libxml_node_object *)intern)->document = NULL;\n \t}\n }\n'}`
responded: The root cause is that both the node and the document may be freed twice, especially when the document node is also referenced as a node. The freeing logic in `dom_objects_free_storage` and the libxml resource decrement functions can overlap, leading to double free.

**Key insight:**  
- In `dom_objects_free_storage`, after calling `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource` or `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref`, only `intern->ptr` is set to NULL, but the underlying `document` pointer in the object may still be non-NULL and reused.
- In `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref`, the document is freed and `object->document` is set to NULL.
- In `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`, after freeing the node, the document is also decremented and potentially freed, but the pointer is not always set to NULL before the next use.

**Best fix:**  
- In `dom_objects_free_storage`, after freeing, set both `intern->ptr` and `((php_libxml_node_object *)intern)->document` to NULL.  
- In `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`, do not attempt to free the document if the node is a document node (since the document will be freed elsewhere).

Let's patch both `dom_objects_free_storage` and `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource` to ensure that:
- The document is only freed once.
- Pointers are set to NULL after freeing.

```diff
--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c
+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
@@ -987,10 +987,16 @@ void dom_objects_free_storage(zend_object *object)
 	if (intern->ptr != NULL && ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node != NULL) {
-		if (((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node)->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && ((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node)->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {
-			php_libxml_node_decrement_resource((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);
-		} else {
-			php_libxml_decrement_node_ptr((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);
-			retcount = php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref((php_libxml_node_object *)intern);
-		}
-		intern->ptr = NULL;
+		xmlNodePtr n = ((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node);
+		if (n->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && n->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {
+			php_libxml_node_decrement_resource((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);
+		} else {
+			php_libxml_decrement_node_ptr((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);
+			retcount = php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref((php_libxml_node_object *)intern);
+		}
+		intern->ptr = NULL;
+		((php_libxml_node_object *)intern)->document = NULL;
 	}
 }
```

Now, let's validate this patch.

