Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c\n+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c\n@@ -993,6 +993,8 @@\n \t\tif (((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node)->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && ((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node)->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {\n \t\t\tphp_libxml_node_decrement_resource((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);\n+\t\t\tintern->document = NULL;\n \t\t} else {\n \t\t\tphp_libxml_decrement_node_ptr((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);\n \t\t\tretcount = php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref((php_libxml_node_object *)intern);\n+\t\t\tintern->document = NULL;\n \t\t}\n \t\tintern->ptr = NULL;\n \t}\n'}`
responded: The root cause is that both the document and node dtors may attempt to free the same document memory, because the `document` pointer is present in both `dom_object` and `php_libxml_node_object`, and the cast in `dom_objects_free_storage` allows both paths to run on the same structure. The document pointer is not set to NULL after freeing in all code paths, so a double free can occur.

**The correct fix** is to ensure that after freeing the document in any path, the pointer is set to NULL. In particular, after calling `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref`, we should always set `object->document = NULL` in the caller as well, since the function may not always set it (if the refcount is not zero).

Additionally, in `dom_objects_free_storage`, after calling `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` or `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`, we should set `intern->document = NULL` to avoid double free if the dtor is called again.

**Here is the patch:**

```diff
--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c
+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
@@ -993,6 +993,8 @@ void dom_objects_free_storage(zend_object *object)
 		if (((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node)->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && ((xmlNodePtr) ((php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr)->node)->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {
 			php_libxml_node_decrement_resource((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);
+			intern->document = NULL;
 		} else {
 			php_libxml_decrement_node_ptr((php_libxml_node_object *) intern);
 			retcount = php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref((php_libxml_node_object *)intern);
+			intern->document = NULL;
 		}
 		intern->ptr = NULL;
 	}
```

This ensures that after freeing, the pointer is always NULL in the object, preventing a double free if the dtor is called again.

Let's validate this patch.

