Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/libxml/libxml.c\n+++ b/ext/libxml/libxml.c\n@@ -1309,7 +1309,13 @@\n \tif (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {\n-\t\t/* Safe to call as if the resource were freed then doc pointer is NULL */\n-\t\tphp_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);\n+\t\t/* Only decrement doc ref for non-document nodes to avoid double free */\n+\t\tif (object->node != NULL) {\n+\t\t\txmlNodePtr nodep = object->node->node;\n+\t\t\tif (nodep && nodep->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && nodep->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {\n+\t\t\t\tphp_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);\n+\t\t\t}\n+\t\t}\n \t}\n }\n'}`
responded: The double free occurs because both `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource` and the "else" branch in `dom_objects_free_storage` can call `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` on the same object, leading to freeing the same `document` pointer twice. The logic in `dom_objects_free_storage` is:

- If the node is not a document node, call `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`, which always calls `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` at the end.
- If the node is a document node, call `php_libxml_decrement_node_ptr` and then `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` directly.

But in the first branch, after calling `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`, the code sets `intern->ptr = NULL;`, but the `document` pointer inside the object may already have been freed and set to NULL by `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref`. If the object is destroyed again, a double free can occur.

**Correct fix:**  
- In `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`, only call `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` for non-document nodes. For document nodes, the decrement should be handled by the caller (as in the "else" branch of `dom_objects_free_storage`).
- This avoids double freeing the document.

Let's patch `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource` to only call `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` for non-document nodes.

```diff
--- a/ext/libxml/libxml.c
+++ b/ext/libxml/libxml.c
@@ -1309,7 +1309,13 @@
 	if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {
-		/* Safe to call as if the resource were freed then doc pointer is NULL */
-		php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);
+		/* Only decrement doc ref for non-document nodes to avoid double free */
+		if (object->node != NULL) {
+			xmlNodePtr nodep = object->node->node;
+			if (nodep && nodep->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && nodep->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {
+				php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);
+			}
+		}
 	}
 }
```

