Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/libxml/libxml.c\n+++ b/ext/libxml/libxml.c\n@@ -1309,8 +1309,14 @@\n-       if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {\n-               /* Safe to call as if the resource were freed then doc pointer is NULL */\n-               php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);\n-       }\n+       if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL && object->node != NULL) {\n+               xmlNodePtr n = object->node->node;\n+               if (n && n->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && n->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {\n+                       /* Only decrement doc ref for non-document nodes */\n+                       php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);\n+               }\n+       }\n'}`
responded: The unconditional call to `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);` in `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource` remains the *persistent* source of the double free, as confirmed by the sanitizer report and code review. All previous attempts to patch by inserting or conditionalizing have failed because the unconditional call was never effectively removed. The memory leak, on the other hand, occurred only when the doc ref was not decremented at all.

**What is the correct patch?**
- In `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`, only decrement the doc ref for non-document nodes.
- In the DOM destructor, keep the current logic: for document nodes, call `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` directly; for other nodes, call `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`.

Let's now *explicitly remove* the unconditional decrement in `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`, replacing it with a conditional that excludes document nodes, as below:

```diff
--- a/ext/libxml/libxml.c
+++ b/ext/libxml/libxml.c
@@ -1309,8 +1309,14 @@
-	if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {
-		/* Safe to call as if the resource were freed then doc pointer is NULL */
-		php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);
-	}
+	if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL && object->node != NULL) {
+		xmlNodePtr n = object->node->node;
+		if (n && n->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && n->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE) {
+			/* Only decrement doc ref for non-document nodes */
+			php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);
+		}
+	}
```

I will now validate this patch alone, without changes to the destructor.

