Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/libxml/libxml.c\n+++ b/ext/libxml/libxml.c\n@@ -1307,10 +1307,17 @@ PHP_LIBXML_API void php_libxml_node_decrement_resource(php_libxml_node_object *object)\n-   }\n-   if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {\n-       /* Safe to call as if the resource were freed then doc pointer is NULL */\n-       php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);\n-   }\n+    }\n+    /* Only decrement doc ref if document is still set after node free */\n+    if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {\n+        php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);\n+    }\n+    /* Ensure double free cannot occur by NULLing out pointers proactively */\n+    if (object != NULL) {\n+        object->node = NULL;\n+        object->document = NULL;\n+    }\n }\n /* }}} */\n'}`
responded: From our investigation, it appears that the actual problematic scenario is when a node being freed by `php_libxml_node_free_resource()` leads to freeing the document via `xmlFreeDoc` in `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref`, and then a later attempt to decrement or free the document again happens from the outer object destructor path (e.g., `dom_objects_free_storage`) through `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref`, resulting in double-free.

Key insight: The only way to safely prevent this is for the document freeing code to signal that the document is already freed and to NULL all references to it *immediately* after freeing. But in this code, the only pointer is `object->document`, and `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` correctly NULLs this after freeing (as can be seen in line 1249). The only way the double-free can occur is if two paths manage to decrement and then both free the same document. 

In the destructor (`dom_objects_free_storage`), we call `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource` or directly call `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref`. In cases where `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource` handles the final reference, it may trigger freeing the document, but `intern->ptr` (the pointer to the node struct) is not NULLed until after both actions in the current code. Therefore, if freeing through one path causes other references to dereference a soon-to-be-freed pointer, double free can result.

**Best solution**: After freeing the node and/or document, aggressively NULL out both `object->node` and `object->document` within `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource` *immediately* after freeing (whether by node or document decrement), not relying on the inner functions. This will prevent any later invocation of the freeing function on an already-freed pointer.

**Let's update `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource` to NULL both `object->node` and `object->document` immediately after freeing and before returning, and make the call to `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` only if `object->document` is still set after node free.**

Here's the improved patch:

```diff
--- a/ext/libxml/libxml.c
+++ b/ext/libxml/libxml.c
@@ -1307,10 +1307,17 @@ PHP_LIBXML_API void php_libxml_node_decrement_resource(php_libxml_node_object *object)
-   }
-   if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {
-       /* Safe to call as if the resource were freed then doc pointer is NULL */
-       php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);
-   }
+    }
+    /* Only decrement doc ref if document is still set after node free */
+    if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {
+        php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);
+    }
+    /* Ensure double free cannot occur by NULLing out pointers proactively */
+    if (object != NULL) {
+        object->node = NULL;
+        object->document = NULL;
+    }
 }
 /* }}} */
```

