Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/libxml/libxml.c\n+++ b/ext/libxml/libxml.c\n@@ -1300,11 +1300,13 @@ PHP_LIBXML_API void php_libxml_node_decrement_resource(php_libxml_node_object *object)\n         ret_refcount = php_libxml_decrement_node_ptr(object);\n         if (ret_refcount == 0) {\n-            php_libxml_node_free_resource(nodep);\n-        } else {\n-            if (obj_node && object == obj_node->_private) {\n-                obj_node->_private = NULL;\n-            }\n+            php_libxml_node_free_resource(nodep);\n+        } else {\n+            if (obj_node && object == obj_node->_private) {\n+                obj_node->_private = NULL;\n+            }\n+            if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {\n+                php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);\n+            }\n         }\n-    }\n-    if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {\n-        /* Safe to call as if the resource were freed then doc pointer is NULL */\n-        php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);\n-    }\n+    }\n }\n /* }}} */\n'}`
responded: From the code inspection, we see that:
- `php_libxml_decrement_node_ptr()` (line 1192+) sets `object->node = NULL;` when its refcount reaches 0 (after freeing).
- `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref()` sets `object->document = NULL;` after freeing.
- In `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`, after the call to `php_libxml_decrement_node_ptr()`, `object->node` may already be NULL if that refcount reached zero.
- When `php_libxml_node_free_resource()` is called, it can end up freeing the document, thus setting the `object->document` pointer to NULL. But, in the higher level, the pointer to `object` in userland could still be alive.

**The real issue**
- In `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource`, on `ret_refcount == 0`, we free the node, then still, we may call `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object)` on a `document` pointer that was already freed as a side-effect of freeing the node resource or the document's last node.
- However, since `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref` is supposed to be idempotent (returns immediately if `object->document == NULL`), this should be safe, UNLESS the relationship between freeing the root node and the document is not strict—i.e., freeing a document's last node does NOT always mean the doc memory has already been properly released.

The key *mistake* in the original `php_libxml_node_decrement_resource` is: 
- If `ret_refcount == 0`, we call `php_libxml_node_free_resource(nodep)` (which may free the document).
- But then, regardless, we always call `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object)`, even though the document may already have been freed by the prior call.

**Canonical fix**:
- Only call `php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object)` if it wasn't just freed via `php_libxml_node_free_resource`.
- Do NOT NULL pointers redundantly in the outer function—they are already properly NULLed when free occurs (as above).

**So, move the document decrement branch into the `else` statement**, so it is not called when `ret_refcount == 0` (last node is about to be freed—let that free routine handle doc reference/lifetime properly). This is the correct fix for double free.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/ext/libxml/libxml.c
+++ b/ext/libxml/libxml.c
@@ -1300,11 +1300,13 @@ PHP_LIBXML_API void php_libxml_node_decrement_resource(php_libxml_node_object *object)
         ret_refcount = php_libxml_decrement_node_ptr(object);
         if (ret_refcount == 0) {
-            php_libxml_node_free_resource(nodep);
-        } else {
-            if (obj_node && object == obj_node->_private) {
-                obj_node->_private = NULL;
-            }
+            php_libxml_node_free_resource(nodep);
+        } else {
+            if (obj_node && object == obj_node->_private) {
+                obj_node->_private = NULL;
+            }
+            if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {
+                php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);
+            }
         }
-    }
-    if (object != NULL && object->document != NULL) {
-        /* Safe to call as if the resource were freed then doc pointer is NULL */
-        php_libxml_decrement_doc_ref(object);
-    }
+    }
 }
